  "server": {
    "name": "io.nyc.bsa",
    "title": "NYC Board of Standards & Appeals (BSA)",
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "description": "Agent-native access to the NYC Board of Standards & Appeals \u2014 zoning applications and their status, written resolutions, the public hearing calendar, pre-application meetings, and the property/zoning-lot index (back to 1916) from NYC Open Data and nyc.gov, plus the net-new ability to file and track a variance / special permit / extension / appeal that today is a paper PDF-form process with no online portal.",
    "instructions": "Use find_applications / get_application to locate BSA cases by borough, application type (BZ variance/special-permit, BZY extension, SOC amendment, Appeal), status, zoning district, council district, or BBL, and get_application_resolution or find_resolutions to reach the written decision (today a linked PDF). find_hearings publishes the public hearing calendar that has no Open Data twin. find_pre_application_meetings covers the pre-filing consultation log. find_zoning_lots looks up a property's BSA history including legacy cases back to 1916. file_variance_application (net-new) files a new case; it requires an authenticated filer and mutates state \u2014 confirm the relief sought, the ZR/GCL section, the premises, the applicant, and the required exhibits with the user before submitting. BSA assigns the calendar number."
  },
